      <memberdef kind="function" id="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a642b41b44970302037fe6626f6054b90_1a642b41b44970302037fe6626f6054b90" prot="public" static="no" const="yes" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>T</type>
        <definition>T integration::Integrator&lt; T &gt;::gregory_omega</definition>
        <argsstring>(int j) const</argsstring>
        <name>gregory_omega</name>
        <qualifiedname>integration::Integrator::gregory_omega</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>j</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><bold> Returns the Gregory weights at the integral boundaries (see <computeroutput><ref refid="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d_1a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d" kindref="member">gregory_weights</ref></computeroutput>). </bold> </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Purpose</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
Returns the weight <formula id="145">$\omega_j$</formula> needed close to the integral boundaries (see <computeroutput>gregory weights</computeroutput>).  <parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>j</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><blockquote><para>Index of the Gregory weight. </para>
</blockquote></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="cntr/integration.hpp" line="405" column="5" bodyfile="cntr/integration.hpp" bodystart="405" bodyend="405"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d_1a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d" prot="public" static="no" const="yes" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <type>T</type>
        <definition>T integration::Integrator&lt; T &gt;::gregory_weights</definition>
        <argsstring>(int n, int j) const</argsstring>
        <name>gregory_weights</name>
        <qualifiedname>integration::Integrator::gregory_weights</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>j</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><bold> Returns the Gregory weights for integration. </bold> </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Purpose</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
The Gregory integration formula of order <formula id="124">$k$</formula> is defined by</para>
<para><formula id="142">\begin{align*}  \int^{x_m}_0 dx \, f(x) = \sum^{\mathrm{max}(k,m)}_{l=0} w_{m,l}\, f(x_l)
\end{align*}</formula></para>
<para>For <formula id="143">$m &gt; 2 k$</formula>, the weights have a simpler form:</para>
<para><formula id="144">\begin{align*} w_{m,j} = \begin{cases} 
 \omega_j &amp; : j \le k \\
  1 &amp; : k &lt; j &lt; m-k \\
 \omega_{m-j} &amp; : j \ge m-k
 \end{cases}
\end{align*}</formula></para>
<para>Here, <formula id="145">$\omega_j$</formula> are tabulated weights for <formula id="146">$0 \le j \le k$</formula>.</para>
<para><computeroutput><ref refid="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d_1a0c816992e749eeeff0817b46ae502e3d" kindref="member">gregory_weights</ref></computeroutput> returns <formula id="147">$w_{n,j}$</formula> for given <formula id="148">$n, j$</formula>. </para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><blockquote><para>Integration runs up to <formula id="149">$x_n$</formula>. </para>
</blockquote></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>j</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Index of the Gregory weight.  </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="cntr/integration.hpp" line="382" column="5" bodyfile="cntr/integration.hpp" bodystart="382" bodyend="390"/>
      </memberdef>
      <memberdef kind="function" id="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a0111a0673a071608ce93e16fcf0e415f_1a0111a0673a071608ce93e16fcf0e415f" prot="public" static="no" const="yes" explicit="no" inline="yes" virt="non-virtual">
        <templateparamlist>
          <param>
            <type>class M</type>
          </param>
        </templateparamlist>
        <type>M</type>
        <definition>M integration::Integrator&lt; T &gt;::integrate</definition>
        <argsstring>(const std::vector&lt; M &gt; &amp;f, int n) const</argsstring>
        <name>integrate</name>
        <qualifiedname>integration::Integrator::integrate</qualifiedname>
        <param>
          <type>const std::vector&lt; M &gt; &amp;</type>
          <declname>f</declname>
        </param>
        <param>
          <type>int</type>
          <declname>n</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para><bold> Integrates a function using Gregory quadrature. </bold> </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Purpose</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
Computes the integral</para>
<para><formula id="157">\begin{align*}  \int^{x_n}_0 dx \, f(x) = h\sum^{\mathrm{max}(k,m)}_{l=0} w_{n,l}\, f(x_l)
\end{align*}</formula></para>
<para>The function <formula id="100">$f$</formula> represents any class <computeroutput>M</computeroutput> for which <computeroutput>M=0</computeroutput> is defined.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>f</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><blockquote><para>A standard vector of class <computeroutput>M</computeroutput> with at least lenght <computeroutput>n+1</computeroutput>. </para>
</blockquote></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The index of the upper integral bound.  </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
        <location file="cntr/integration.hpp" line="474" column="17" bodyfile="cntr/integration.hpp" bodystart="474" bodyend="493"/>
