        <briefdescription>
<para><bold> Returns the the weight needed for polynomial differentiation. </bold> </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><simplesect kind="par"><title>Purpose</title><para></para>
</simplesect>
Assuming the function <formula id="132">$f(x)$</formula> is given through points <formula id="127">$\{(x_l,f(x_l),l=0,\dots,k)\}$</formula>\ with <formula id="128">$x_{l+1}-x_{l}=h$</formula>, polynomial differentiation is defined by</para>
<para><formula id="133">\begin{align*}  \frac{d}{dx}f(x)\big|_{x_i} = \frac{1}{h}\sum^k_{l=0} c_{i,l}\, f(x_l)
\end{align*}</formula></para>
<para><computeroutput><ref refid="classintegration_1_1Integrator_a8737cc79dbcd9f53508c705ae8f09da8_1a8737cc79dbcd9f53508c705ae8f09da8" kindref="member">poly_differentiation</ref></computeroutput> returns the coefficient <formula id="134">$c_{i,l}$</formula> for given indicies <formula id="135">$i,l$</formula>.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>i</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para><blockquote><para>First index of coefficients. </para>
</blockquote></para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>l</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Second index of coefficients.  </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
